reviews.text:
Vincenzo's pizza is like any other pizza we've ever had. Somehow they managed to make it crisp and doughy. At the same time. The toppings are fresh and flavorful.

On a humorous note, we ordered an extra large pizza last week and before we placed the order, we were asked if we were sure we knew how big it was. We were and we proceeded with paying for the pizza. When my husband brought it home, it barely fit through our door. No, that is not an exaggeration. So if you're looking for a super large pizza to feed a small army, consider the Vincenzo's extra large.

Online ordering from my phone was so easy and quick. Their website is also very clear and easy to navigate. The takeout order was fast. The BBQ chicken wings is good, not too sweet. My only concern is their pepperoni topping, it‚Äôs very very salty for my taste, not good for people on a low-salt diet or with high blood pressure ü§£ Overall though, I still like Vincenzo‚Äôs and maybe avoid the pepperoni next time.

Pizza is epic, probably the best in SCV. Wings are a solid 8/10. Salads and the cheese bread are really good. Not a fan of the jalape√±o poppers or the mozzarella sticks, the breading tastes off and feels like it was frozen. That being said, I came for the pizza, not the fried food. They have a decent size sitting area and a couple of chairs outside as well.

This is the best pizza I‚Äôve had out here in CA, (I‚Äôm originally from East Coast). Probably top 5 in my lifetime! The pizza was delicious. The
sauce was perfect and the stuffed crust was outstanding! 5 stars!

Definitely one of those places that feels like it came out of the 70s. Food was amazing even if the restaurant isn't shiny and new. Amazing toppings and an almost perfect crust style. Would definitely go back if we visit again. Oh did I forget to mention the garlic cheese bread?

detailedReviews.author: Rick Lupert
detailedReviews.text:
We'd been hearing about Vincenzo's ever since we moved to the Santa Clarita Valley a few years back. We're always looking for great NY Style pizza and they can stretch a pie thin to sort of kind of get you in that direction.

You order at the counter (which may be hard to find if you've never been there before...you have to enter the dining room, walk through it, take a couple of lefts before you get there.) Then they bring your food to the table.

We ordered a medium cheese stretched thin...there's always a risk that pizza places don't put enough sauce on a pie...we really like to taste the sauce...I asked about this and they said they'd put a little extra on ours. What came to the table didn't have much sauce on it and was slightly overcooked. It wasn't terrible, but it didn't really achieve the NYC style pie we were looking for.

The Cheese Garlic Bread was good...served on Texas-Style toast. We also had a green salad which had lots of croutons and some cheese on it...basic but good enough.

I think we're still pining for excellent NY style pizza up here. Vincenzo's wasn't quite it. It's nice that they'll stretch their pies thin...the overall dated atmosphere of the room and the many years the place has been there left us thinking this place may have had a hey-day which it left behind a while ago.
